abstract: The top 200 chief executives, who make more than last year, are holding meetings with President Trump, who is considering rolling back Dodd-Frank regulations.
snippet: The top 200 chief executives, who make more than last year, are holding meetings with President Trump, who is considering rolling back Dodd-Frank regulations.
lead_paragraph: Pay packages for America’s top executives once again climbed in 2016 after slipping the year before.

abstract: After 28 hours in Israel and the West Bank, President Trump was convinced he had partners in peace in Benjamin Netanyahu and Mahmoud Abbas. However, he did not reveal what, if anything, was behind it.
snippet: After 28 hours in Israel and the West Bank, President Trump was convinced he had partners in peace in Benjamin Netanyahu and Mahmoud Abbas. However, he did not reveal what, if anything, was behind it.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — In case there was any doubt, President Trump made it exceedingly clear: He wants a deal. “I intend to do everything I can,” he said on Tuesday.

abstract: The president’s effort will test whether a career of business-deal-making can be translated into progress in the world of international diplomacy.
snippet: The president’s effort will test whether a career of business-deal-making can be translated into progress in the world of international diplomacy.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — President Trump began a two-day visit to Israel on Monday with a blunt assessment for Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu: If Israel really wants peace with its Arab neighbors, the cost will be resolving the generations-old standoff with the Palestinians.

abstract: “S.N.L.” paid homage to itself by having Mr. Baldwin sing Leonard Cohen’s “Hallelujah.” The host, Dwayne Johnson, considered a presidential run with Tom Hanks.
snippet: “S.N.L.” paid homage to itself by having Mr. Baldwin sing Leonard Cohen’s “Hallelujah.” The host, Dwayne Johnson, considered a presidential run with Tom Hanks.
lead_paragraph: It was a night of milestones on “Saturday Night Live,” which in the final episode of its 42nd season, said goodbye to the longtime cast members Bobby Moynihan (who is joining the CBS sitcom “Me, Myself & I”) and Vanessa Bayer (who confirmed her departure in a bittersweet Instagram post).

abstract: While party leaders in Washington focus on President Trump’s troubles, candidates in the states are trying to devise a message to reach the voters they need to win back.
snippet: While party leaders in Washington focus on President Trump’s troubles, candidates in the states are trying to devise a message to reach the voters they need to win back.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the nation’s capital was rocked by revelation after revelation from the investigation into any connection between the Trump campaign and Russia, Democrats in Washington were focused on what they saw as nothing less than saving the republic.

headline_main: Outside Washington’s ‘Blazing Inferno,’ Democrats Seek an Agenda
headline_print_headline: To Win at Home, Democrats Put Aside Washington’s ‘Blazing Inferno’

abstract: From President Trump and Sean Spicer to Hillary Clinton and politics in America, “S.N.L.” scored huge ratings and became appointment television again.
snippet: From President Trump and Sean Spicer to Hillary Clinton and politics in America, “S.N.L.” scored huge ratings and became appointment television again.
lead_paragraph: Alec Baldwin pursing his lips, squinting his eyes, saying “Jina.” Melissa McCarthy plowing a podium into a crowd of reporters. Kate McKinnon pivoting from a self-absorbed Hillary Clinton to a deer-in-the-headlights Kellyanne Conway.

abstract: Mr. Burr, the unobtrusive chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee, is moving into a spotlight he never expected and does not seem to relish.
snippet: Mr. Burr, the unobtrusive chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee, is moving into a spotlight he never expected and does not seem to relish.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The premonition came in a Winston-Salem conference room, on an otherwise happy election night in 2004, before Richard M. Burr of North Carolina had even declared victory in his bid to join the Senate.

abstract: The case of John Dalli, a former commissioner, stretches across continents and highlights the European Union’s limited reach in matters of wrongdoing in Brussels.
snippet: The case of John Dalli, a former commissioner, stretches across continents and highlights the European Union’s limited reach in matters of wrongdoing in Brussels.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — When Regina L. Hayes, a retiree in Roebuck, S.C., a small town outside Spartanburg, transferred $75,000 from her savings to an investment fund, she thought she was helping Christian miners in Africa fend off competition from conglomerates. She was promised a return of 10 percent a year.

abstract: Encores! makes a marvelous if last-ditch case for the cult musical based on “The Iliad” and “The Odyssey.”
snippet: Encores! makes a marvelous if last-ditch case for the cult musical based on “The Iliad” and “The Odyssey.”
lead_paragraph: To make a cult, it takes a failure. On that count, “The Golden Apple,” a musical retelling of “The Iliad” and “The Odyssey” set in Washington State around 1900, certainly qualifies. Though it opened to positive reviews at the Phoenix Theater in 1954, and was the first Off Broadway musical ever to transfer to Broadway, it flopped almost as soon as it arrived.

abstract: Book clubs can be the epicenter of fierce friendships and enmity; a breeding ground for resentments large and small.
snippet: Book clubs can be the epicenter of fierce friendships and enmity; a breeding ground for resentments large and small.
lead_paragraph: Michael Goldspiel is an inspired educator and a most cheerful fellow, a golden retriever among men. The assistant superintendent of schools in Roslyn, N.Y., he was describing plans for his new book club. It was going to be great, he told me. Not like his last club. His last club, forget it: “If I can’t make the occasional joke about the text or myself, I’m not interested.”
